# <%= current_page.data.title %>

Welcome to the Crime Platform onboarding process. This guide will walk you through obtaining access to non-live and/or live tenants step by step.

## Overview

The onboarding journey consists of the following steps:

1. [Prepare: Generate Key Pairs](01-generate-keys.html) - Create your GPG and SSH keys
2. [Submit: Request Access](02-request-access.html) - Raise a PR with your public keys
3. [Review: Get Approved](03-get-approved.html) - Platform Operations team reviews your request
4. [Configure: Run ADO Pipeline](04-run-pipeline.html) - Execute the deployment pipeline
5. [Decrypt: Retrieve Credentials](05-decrypt-credentials.html) - Decrypt your password
6. [Setup: Azure Portal](06-azure-portal.html) - Access Azure and configure MFA
7. [Secure: VPN & DNS](07-vpn-dns-config.html) - Configure your VPN connection and DNS
8. [Access: Configure SSH](08-ssh-config.html) - Set up SSH for platform access
9. [Secret: Obtain Keys](09-obtain-secrets.html) - Retrieve Google Authenticator and OpenVPN secrets
10. [Validate: Verify Access](10-validation.html) - Confirm everything is working

